# Modern browsers only - ES2020+ features are natively supported
# This completely eliminates polyfills for Array.at, flat, flatMap, Object.fromEntries, etc.

# Target only browsers that support ES2020+ natively
# These browsers support: Array.at, flat, flatMap, Object.fromEntries, Object.hasOwn, String.trimStart/End
Chrome >= 92
Firefox >= 90
Safari >= 15.4
Edge >= 92
iOS >= 15.4
Samsung >= 16
Opera >= 78

# Exclude legacy browsers explicitly
not IE 11
not op_mini all
not dead
